; #1142 bug class: per-posting metadata interleaved between
; postings of the same transaction. Earlier versions of the
; formatter used `txn_start_line + 1 + posting_idx` line
; arithmetic and wrongly-attributed indented metadata lines, which
; either dropped them or migrated them onto the wrong posting.
; The CST migration's per-posting span captures the metadata
; structurally; this fixture pins that contract.
2024-01-15 * "FX transfer with per-posting effective dates"
  Assets:USD  -100.00 USD
    effective_date: 2024-01-16
    rate_source: "ECB"
  Assets:EUR    92.00 EUR
    effective_date: 2024-01-17
    rate_source: "ECB"
